item.title: October Desktop 2009 1
item.author: invalid@example.com (Teraforce)
item.dc:creator: Teraforce
item.content:encoded: My first desktop for October 2009. Wallpaper is from the PS2 game known as Gradius V. The skin is Wisp. It was cool for a while, but then it just got too "blue" for me (which isn't really an October color anyway).

item.title: October Desktop 2009 2
item.author: invalid@example.com (Teraforce)
item.dc:creator: Teraforce
item.content:encoded: The wallpaper this time is a picture I took of someone roasting marshmallows by our annual homecoming bonfire (which is probably 40ft tall or so). No skin is used, though I did use the Maple color scheme to match the wallpaper. EXIF Data of Wallpaper: Camera: Nikon D80 Lens: AF-S VR Nikkor 70-300mm f/4.5-5.6G @ 300mm Aperture: f/5.6 Shutter speed: 1/125 sec ISO: 400 Exposure Comp: -0.5 Mode: Manual Exposure

item.title: Invalid MS-DOS function in Windows XP
item.author: invalid@example.com (Teraforce)
item.dc:creator: Teraforce
item.content:encoded: This is what I get when I try to copy a video from my digital camera's SD card onto my HD. I thought MS-DOS was killed with the introduction of Windows XP. I guess not!!!!!!
